00:35:34.720 --> 00:35:37.560
because there's a lot
of risk in the time

00:35:37.560 --> 00:35:42.640 position:56%
between when a doctor sees a patient
first and when the medicines work,

00:35:42.640 --> 00:35:45.680
a lot of risky things
like suicide and other,

00:35:45.680 --> 00:35:47.530
you know, dramatic negative acts.

00:35:47.530 --> 00:35:49.250
So, we're very interested in that.

00:35:49.250 --> 00:35:52.520
That said, the antidepressants
we have

00:35:52.520 --> 00:35:56.120
to had now do do things very early.

00:35:56.120 --> 00:36:01.550
I write about a doctor at Oxford
in England who has used a test

00:36:01.550 --> 00:36:05.440 position:56%
of perception, how do you evaluate
kind of pictures and which you ought

00:36:05.440 --> 00:36:08.690
to see helpful things but
depressed people might not.

00:36:08.690 --> 00:36:11.680
And he's giving people half
doses of antidepressants,

00:36:11.680 --> 00:36:16.950
and within three hours,
their outlook changes

00:36:16.950 --> 00:36:18.500
and their self-assessment.

00:36:18.500 --> 00:36:20.060
So, there are some early effects.

00:36:20.060 --> 00:36:23.810
And one of the theories about
how these medicines work is

00:36:23.810 --> 00:36:28.060
that they loosen up the brain in
some way, but a lot of what goes

00:36:28.060 --> 00:36:32.140
on in recovery from the
