doctors try to write a note

00:37:06.040 --> 00:37:09.480
to pharmaceutical companies
to override that,

00:37:09.480 --> 00:37:13.990
it's been my experience that more
and more often they're rejected.

00:37:13.990 --> 00:37:15.290
&gt;&gt; Dr. Peter Kramer: Right.

00:37:15.290 --> 00:37:16.590
&gt;&gt; What is it about the generics?

00:37:16.590 --> 00:37:17.890 position:56%
And I know the difference maybe on--

00:37:17.890 --> 00:37:24.120
between the generic and the
one that was originally patent.

00:37:24.120 --> 00:37:27.340
But I'm just wondering, are
you aware of this as a problem

00:37:27.340 --> 00:37:28.760
because I see it quite a bit?

00:37:28.760 --> 00:37:30.060
&gt;&gt; Dr. Peter Kramer: Yes.

00:37:30.060 --> 00:37:32.370
I mean, doctors worry
when a medicine goes

00:37:32.370 --> 00:37:37.750
from a company primarily making it
to a generic manufacture making it

00:37:37.750 --> 00:37:40.920
that the standards of the
Food and Drug Administration

00:37:40.920 --> 00:37:45.910
for what constitutes equivalence
are either loose or even

00:37:45.910 --> 00:37:48.900
when they're fairly
demanding that down the road,

00:37:48.900 --> 00:37:54.140
not enough drugs are retested so
that people on the generic don't do

00:37:54.140 --> 00:37:56.860
as well as they did when
they were on brand name drug.

00:37:56.860 --> 00:37:59.030
On the other hand, of
course, we're very worried

00:37:59.030 --> 00:38:01.840
if doctors are being
influenced by advertising

00:38:01.840 --> 00:38:05.690 position:56%
and prescribing brand name drugs and
making medical care more expensive

00:38:05.690 --> 00:38:08.130
where generics are just as good.

00:38:08.130 --> 00:38:11.860
And the answer is it just really
is not enough science on this,

00:38:11.860 --> 00:38:15.980
but every doctor sees it, you know,
of course where it's dramatic is

00:38:15.980 --> 00:38:20.670
in neurology where drug
against epilepsy becomes generic

00:38:20.670 --> 00:38:23.500
and doesn't work as well and
people start having seizures again.

00:38:23.500 --> 00:38:26.530
You know, you see that whereas
when people kind of fade

00:38:26.530 --> 00:38:29.780 position:56%
into having more depressive
symptoms and become more depressive.

00:38:29.780 --> 00:38:33.270
It's not as dramatic and
as hard to know about.

00:38:33.270 --> 00:38:38.170
I think with Wellbutrin which is a
drug that works by different means,

00:38:38.170 --> 00:38:42.250
Bupropion, when that became
generic, there were patients

00:38:42.250 --> 00:38:46.110
who certainly said they
weren't doing as well on it.

00:38:46.110 --> 00:38:50.520
I have patients who are on
the brand name of Wellbutrin.

00:38:50.520 --> 00:38:55.110 position:56%
On the other hand, lots of people
do well on the generic when Concerta

00:38:55.110 --> 00:38:59.860
which is a complicated form
of Ritalin that kids use

00:38:59.860 --> 00:39:02.530
because it has a certain
curve of release.

00:39:02.530 --> 00:39:06.610
So, it kind of covers [inaudible]
very well became generic.

00:39:06.610 --> 00:39:10.600
I noticed in adult patients
that it wasn't working as well.

00:39:10.600 --> 00:39:14.380
And the pharmacists reassured
me and then the FDA did say

00:39:14.380 --> 00:39:15.780
that the generic-- three

00:39:15.780 --> 00:39:18.060
of the manufacturers weren't
doing a good enough job

00:39:18.060 --> 00:39:20.590 position:56%
and they had to sort of rejigger it.

00:39:20.590 --> 00:39:24.100
But the generic still doesn't
have the same engineering

00:39:24.100 --> 00:39:25.400
that the brand name has.

00:39:25.400 --> 00:39:29.730 position:56%
So, you know, we do worry about that
and it's across all of medicine.

00:39:29.730 --> 00:39:31.730
And frankly, not enough
is known about it.

00:39:31.730 --> 00:39:36.480
It's hard to know what is patient's
anxiety and what is biochemistry.

00:39:36.480 --> 00:39:38.440
&gt;&gt; That supports what
I've read so far.

00:39:38.440 --> 00:39:41.310
So, that sounds occurring.

00:39:42.340 --> 00:39:43.640
Thank you.

00:39:43.640 --> 00:39:47.050
&gt;&gt; I see situations
where people say that--

00:39:47.050 --> 00:39:52.040
or think that psychotherapy is
